<a name="This_is_for_general_information_about_producing_and_distributing_Mods."></a><h2> This is for general information about producing and distributing Mods. </h2>
<p><b>Auto Download (v1.3 only).</b><br />
<a href="/web/20070729231805/http://zerowing.idsoftware.com/linux/doom/AutoDownload" class='external free' title="http://zerowing.idsoftware.com/linux/doom/AutoDownload">http://zerowing.idsoftware.com/linux/doom/AutoDownload</a>
</p><p><b>AddonPaks (v1.3 only)</b><br />
<a href="/web/20070729231805/http://zerowing.idsoftware.com/linux/doom/AddonPaks" class='external free' title="http://zerowing.idsoftware.com/linux/doom/AddonPaks">http://zerowing.idsoftware.com/linux/doom/AddonPaks</a>
</p><p><b>fs_game_base (v1.3 only)</b><br />
<a href="/web/20070729231805/http://zerowing.idsoftware.com/linux/doom/fs_game_base" class='external free' title="http://zerowing.idsoftware.com/linux/doom/fs_game_base">http://zerowing.idsoftware.com/linux/doom/fs_game_base</a>
</p>
<a name="Hints.2FTips_for_Modders"></a><h3> Hints/Tips for Modders </h3>
<p>You should install Doom 3 into a directory with no spaces (for instance "d:\doom3") to avoid potential problems later on.
Although you can work in the \doom3\base directory it's strongly recommended that you create a new mod directory (eg "d:\doom3\mymod") to keep the Doom 3 base folder clean of custom files. It should only contain the original <a href="/web/20070729231805/http://www.modwiki.net/wiki/PK4_%28file_format%29" title="PK4 (file format)">.PK4</a> files and the directories created at runtime by Doom 3.
</p><p>The original Doom 3 declaration files come with a lot of redundant, deprecated and obsolete or nonworking entries so it's recommended that you use <a href="/web/20070729231805/http://www.modwiki.net/wiki/Eutectic%27s_clean_paks" title="Eutectic's clean paks">eutectic's clean paks</a>.
</p><p>You can create shortcuts to get into the editor or game quickly:
</p>
<pre>editing: d:\doom3\doom3.exe +disconnect +set r_fullscreen 0 +editor +set fs_game mymod
testing: d:\doom3\doom3.exe +disconnect +set r_fullscreen 1 +set fs_game mymod +map mymap
</pre>
<p>If you use <a href="/web/20070729231805/http://www.modwiki.net/wiki/Antialiasing" title="Antialiasing">antialiasing</a> in Doom 3 you'll want to add "+set <a href="/web/20070729231805/http://www.modwiki.net/wiki/R_multiSamples_%28cvar%29" title="R multiSamples (cvar)">r_multisamples</a> 0" at the end of the editing shortcut and "+set r_multisamples X" at the end of the testing shortcut (if you wish to keep using AntiAliasing in-game). Make sure you substitute the X with the number of samples you use (2, 4, 8, 16).
</p>
<div><a href="/web/20070729231805/http://www.modwiki.net/wiki/Image:D3square_25.png" class="image" title="Image:D3square_25.png"><img src="/web/20070729231805im_/http://www.modwiki.net/w/images/2/23/D3square_25.png" alt="Image:D3square_25.png" width="25" height="25" longdesc="/wiki/Image:D3square_25.png" /></a> <b>Note:</b> Doom 3: ROE only: <dl><dd><i>If you are modding for the Doom 3: Resurrection of Evil expansion then add "+set fs_game_base d3xp" at the end of both shortcuts.</i></dd></dl></div>
<div><a href="/web/20070729231805/http://www.modwiki.net/wiki/Image:D3square_25.png" class="image" title="Image:D3square_25.png"><img src="/web/20070729231805im_/http://www.modwiki.net/w/images/2/23/D3square_25.png" alt="Image:D3square_25.png" width="25" height="25" longdesc="/wiki/Image:D3square_25.png" /></a> <b>Note:</b> Doom 3 only: <dl><dd><i>Pre-1.3 versions of Doom 3 would copy your "doomkey" (and "xpkey" if you have the Doom 3: Resurrection of Evil expansion) file to all your mod folders. This means you have to be careful that you do NOT distribute this file along with your mod if you are still using these older versions of the game. Even if you upgraded to v1.3 you should make sure your mod folder does not have this file.</i></dd></dl></div>
<p><br />
</p>
<a name="Putting_it_all_Together"></a><h2>Putting it all Together</h2>
<p>After you have all your assets done you can automatically generate a batch file to create compressed versions of .<a href="/web/20070729231805/http://www.modwiki.net/wiki/TGA_%28file_format%29" title="TGA (file format)">TGA</a> and .<a href="/web/20070729231805/http://www.modwiki.net/wiki/WAV_%28file_format%29" title="WAV (file format)">WAV</a> files. To do so you must complete the following:
</p>
<ul><li><a href="/web/20070729231805/http://www.modwiki.net/wiki/Com_makingBuild_%28cvar%29" title="Com makingBuild (cvar)">com_makingBuild</a> 1
</li><li><a href="/web/20070729231805/http://www.modwiki.net/wiki/Image_useOfflineCompression_%28cvar%29" title="Image useOfflineCompression (cvar)">image_useOfflineCompression</a> 1
</li><li><a href="/web/20070729231805/http://www.modwiki.net/wiki/StartBuild_%28console_command%29" title="StartBuild (console command)">startBuild</a>
</li><li><a href="/web/20070729231805/http://www.modwiki.net/wiki/Map_%28console_command%29" title="Map (console command)">map</a> &lt;mapname&gt;
</li><li><a href="/web/20070729231805/http://www.modwiki.net/w/index.php?title=FinishBuild_%28console_command%29&amp;action=edit" class="new" title="FinishBuild (console command)">finishBuild</a>
</li></ul>
<p>You should now have two batch files present: <i>makedds.bat</i> and <i>makeogg.bat</i>. You must do this from your mod hierarchy as it will not work if you already put your assets into .PK4 files (see below).
</p>
<a name="Distribution"></a><h2>Distribution</h2>
<p>You should pack all your custom files into .PK4 files. When you distribute your .PK4 file with your mod or map you should make sure that the root directory in the pack file only contains the following files:
</p>
<ul><li><i>addon.conf</i>  - See link above.
</li><li><i>description.txt</i> - optional text file for mod folder description (only needed for mods in seperate folders).
</li><li><i>binary.conf</i> - This MUST be included if the .PK4 contains gamex86.dll / gamex86.so / gameppc.dylib - without the binary.conf Doom 3 will not load your modded binary (this became mandatory since v1.3).
</li><li><i>&lt;mod/mapname&gt;_readme.txt</i> - your readme file, it's a bad idea to call this just readme.txt as anyone extracting the pack contents may overwrite an existing readme.txt file.
</li></ul>
<a name="Achieving_Better_Compression"></a><h3>Achieving Better Compression</h3>
<p>Even if you use the maximum compression possible in .PK4 files it will never rival the compression ratios possible by <a href="/web/20070729231805/http://www.win-rar.com/" class='external text' title="http://www.win-rar.com">WinRar</a> for instance. However the following will:
</p>
<ol><li>Create your .PK4 files with the <i>store</i> compression factor.
</li><li>RAR all your .PK4 files with maximum compression. (You may want to create a SFX archive, instead of straight .RAR so people won't have to download WinRar to open it; which can also double as an installer for your mod.)
</li></ol>
<p>You should now be able to distribute a much smaller file than if you had used max compression for the .PK4 files.
</p><div class="printfooter">
